Time Reporting App

Installation

1. Clone this repository: git clone https://github.com/hemajayachandran/time_reporting.git
2. cd into time_reporting/time_reporting
3. Install Python 3.8.5
4. Install virtualenv "python3 -m pip install --user virtualenv"
5. Create a new virtual environment "python3 -m venv <virtualenvname>"
6. Activate virtualenv "source <virtualenvname>/bin/activate"
7. Install Django==2.1.5
8. Run "python3 manage.py runserver" and open the server mentioned in the terminal console "http://127.0.0.1:8000/login"

If you see the login page, the app deployed successfully.

9. You can signup for a new user, login(email id) and submit the timesheet.
10. Create an admin login by running python3 manage.py createsuperuser
11. Open http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin with the admin credentials
12. Go to Hours, you can open the corresponding record and mark it as 'Completed'. After this user won't be able to edit the timesheet.

Functional requirements

1. REPORTING_DATE is set inside time_reporting/settings.py
2. MAX_HOURS and database settings are also within settings.py. The default database 'sqlite3' is considered here.
3. Loggers for monthly, yearly and error have also been defined under settings.py.
